I was in that queue

506
00:47:09.335 --> 00:47:11.470
and people even
brought sleeping bags.


507
00:47:11.537 --> 00:47:14.807
Some people slept out there
all night.


508
00:47:14.907 --> 00:47:17.209
They were taking it in turns.

509
00:47:17.310 --> 00:47:19.612
Two hours each and then switch.

510
00:47:19.712 --> 00:47:23.282
I remember at one point
the Police went by,


511
00:47:23.382 --> 00:47:25.017
maybe somebody said something,

512
00:47:25.084 --> 00:47:27.486
and then charged

513
00:47:27.587 --> 00:47:29.021
scattering the queue

514
00:47:29.088 --> 00:47:31.057
only for it to reform later on.

515
00:47:31.123 --> 00:47:35.661
And the next day they rushed in

516
00:47:35.728 --> 00:47:40.366
as if they'd been tied down,
everyone running to get there first.


517
00:47:43.302 --> 00:47:47.173
When the tickets
were supposed to go on sale,


518
00:47:47.873 --> 00:47:51.110
they called me
and said there was a problem,


519
00:47:51.744 --> 00:47:54.213
there were no tickets
left at the Carrión.


520
00:47:55.047 --> 00:47:58.451
"No tickets? But they're
not even on sale yet."


521
00:47:58.551 --> 00:48:03.189
"Yes, but there are no tickets
for 'A Clockwork Orange'."


522
00:48:03.823 --> 00:48:08.227
We went straight over.

523
00:48:08.294 --> 00:48:13.366
When we saw the queue,
Carmelo and I got a shock.


524
00:48:13.466 --> 00:48:15.835
We thought:
"This is going to get messy."


525
00:48:17.403 --> 00:48:19.772
We asked the ticket operator
what was wrong.


526
00:48:19.872 --> 00:48:23.609
"Sir, the owner of the cinema,"

527
00:48:23.709 --> 00:48:28.314
has given all of the tickets
for 'A Clockwork Orange'


528
00:48:28.381 --> 00:48:32.051
to their friends, contacts, etc.

529
00:48:32.151 --> 00:48:34.487
"And there are none left."

530
00:48:34.587 --> 00:48:38.591
None of the people waiting
outside


531
00:48:39.125 --> 00:48:41.627
could get in
because there were no tickets.


532
00:48:41.927 --> 00:48:43.329
"What do you mean?"

533
00:48:43.429 --> 00:48:45.731
What am I going to do
with all of these people


534
00:48:45.831 --> 00:48:48.668
who have been queueing
for over 24 hours


535
00:48:48.734 --> 00:48:51.737
"waiting to see the film?"

536
00:48:51.804 --> 00:48:53.873
"I don't know,
there are no tickets."


537
00:48:53.939 --> 00:48:58.110
They cancelled the tickets that
had been assigned beforehand.


538
00:48:58.444 --> 00:49:00.246
They brought out some new
tickets,


539
00:49:00.346 --> 00:49:03.382
gave them
to the ticket operator and said:


540
00:49:03.449 --> 00:49:05.951
"Use these ones".

541
00:49:06.686 --> 00:49:11.991
The poor woman looked like
she'd just seen a ghost.


542
00:49:12.058 --> 00:49:15.895
He had given one thousand
tickets


543
00:49:16.328 --> 00:49:20.533
to all the people
who wanted to see the film


544
00:49:20.633 --> 00:49:22.034
and hadn't queued.

545
00:49:22.101 --> 00:49:26.272
It had a big impact
but it was well organised


546
00:49:26.338 --> 00:49:27.773
and sorted out properly.

547
00:49:27.873 --> 00:49:32.111
The tickets sold out
immediately.


548
00:49:32.178 --> 00:49:36.549
The only inconvenience, besides
spending the night outside,


549
00:49:36.982 --> 00:49:39.652
was that lots of people in the
queue


550
00:49:40.052 --> 00:49:44.790
were planning to buy ten or
twelve tickets for their friends


551
00:49:45.324 --> 00:49:48.627
but were met
with the unpleasant surprise


552
00:49:48.694 --> 00:49:53.365
that the organisers were only
selling two tickets per person.


553
00:49:53.466 --> 00:49:57.570
So the friend that got to the
front was only given two tickets


554
00:49:57.670 --> 00:49:59.105
to share with everyone...

555
00:50:00.172 --> 00:50:02.508
it was a big disappointment.

556
00:50:03.075 --> 00:50:07.012
We were such good friends that
we drew straws for the tickets


557
00:50:07.913 --> 00:50:10.583
and my husband and I
ended up with them


558
00:50:11.050 --> 00:50:12.685
so we went to see it

559
00:50:12.785 --> 00:50:15.087
and our expectations were very
high.


560
00:50:19.058 --> 00:50:21.927
There was an organised way
to pick up the tickets


561
00:50:22.027 --> 00:50:24.730
and enter the cinema
in an orderly fashion.


562
00:50:25.498 --> 00:50:27.767
My role at the cinema

563
00:50:27.867 --> 00:50:32.805
was to make sure nothing went
wrong during the screening.


564
00:50:32.905 --> 00:50:36.442
The city was divided:
those who were excited


565
00:50:36.542 --> 00:50:39.178
and those who sat at the front
saying the rosary,


566
00:50:39.245 --> 00:50:40.713
they couldn't believe it.

567
00:50:41.147 --> 00:50:43.048
Peace wasn't guaranteed.

568
00:50:43.149 --> 00:50:47.853
The previous year a film
by Carlos Saura had been shown,


569
00:50:47.953 --> 00:50:49.355
'Cousin Angelica'.

570
00:50:49.421 --> 00:50:53.459
I went to see it in Gijón
and they stopped the film


571
00:50:53.526 --> 00:50:58.497
because Falange,
very right-wing people


572
00:50:58.831 --> 00:51:01.467
didn't like how they were
portrayed.


573
00:51:01.534 --> 00:51:06.071
The Police had their eye on it.

574
00:51:06.138 --> 00:51:12.111
There was a small group of
anti-riot police in the cinema.


575
00:51:12.178 --> 00:51:14.446
They were keeping an eye
on what was going on.


576
00:51:17.349 --> 00:51:21.787
I decided to go up
to the projection booth


577
00:51:22.621 --> 00:51:26.492
to make sure that nothing went
wrong


578
00:51:26.592 --> 00:51:29.094
and that everything
was running smoothly.


579
00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:37.036
I watched it from up here,
from where we're filming.


580
00:51:37.770 --> 00:51:39.505
It was full to the rafters.

581
00:51:39.572 --> 00:51:42.575
Everyone was absolutely silent,
there wasn't a sound.


582
00:51:42.675 --> 00:51:44.643
Silent and excited

583
00:51:44.743 --> 00:51:47.980
to see what we'd waited
all night for,


584
00:51:48.047 --> 00:51:51.450
what it was like,
we didn't want to miss a thing.


585
00:52:20.913 --> 00:52:23.515
Half way through the film,

586
00:52:24.116 --> 00:52:26.585
the Police rang me

587
00:52:26.652 --> 00:52:29.455
to say there was a bomb
in the cinema.


588
00:52:30.689 --> 00:52:31.790
Oh my God...

589
00:52:32.324 --> 00:52:35.728
Back then, bomb alerts

590
00:52:36.128 --> 00:52:39.298
were relatively common

591
00:52:39.665 --> 00:52:45.304
at cultural and problematic
events.


592
00:52:46.305 --> 00:52:49.008
Calling up and saying:

593
00:52:49.108 --> 00:52:52.211
"Hey, there's a bomb
in such a such place"


594
00:52:52.311 --> 00:52:55.614
meant the activity would be
stopped


595
00:52:55.714 --> 00:53:00.452
and implied no risk
for the person who called it in.


596
00:53:01.487 --> 00:53:04.189
I decided to take a chance
and I told him:


597
00:53:04.256 --> 00:53:06.926
"Look, sir, I'm sorry"

598
00:53:07.026 --> 00:53:11.764
but I'll be held responsible
for not stopping the screening.


599
00:53:12.564 --> 00:53:14.733
We're half way through,

600
00:53:14.833 --> 00:53:16.936
and after everything that's
happened,


601
00:53:17.870 --> 00:53:21.507
"we'll see it through to the
end."


602
00:53:31.016 --> 00:53:32.551
I was impressed by the film.

603
00:53:35.187 --> 00:53:36.755
It was visually striking.

604
00:53:37.389 --> 00:53:41.293
The whole set design is incredible.
It's brutalist.


605
00:53:43.095 --> 00:53:45.531
The setting is so modern.

606
00:53:45.631 --> 00:53:46.665
The colours,

607
00:53:47.499 --> 00:53:48.701
the clothes...

608
00:53:48.767 --> 00:53:53.706
Pop iconography was so
interesting to us back then.


609
00:53:54.707 --> 00:53:56.809
I thought
it was absolutely fantastic,


610
00:53:56.909 --> 00:53:59.511
very clever, very well done,
very well performed.


611
00:53:59.578 --> 00:54:03.449
Malcolm McDowell with that
evil face and that eye...


612
00:55:19.858 --> 00:55:23.495
It's also striking
the way they try to cure him.


613
00:55:27.833 --> 00:55:31.336
With his eyes held open

614
00:55:31.403 --> 00:55:36.708
to make him watch the scenes
of violence and everything...


615
00:56:48.313 --> 00:56:50.215
I remember that the music...

616
00:56:51.617 --> 00:56:55.954
perfectly matched
the scenes of violence.


617
00:57:14.139 --> 00:57:15.574
It made me feel quite ill,

618
00:57:15.674 --> 00:57:18.443
I'd never seen violence like it.

619
00:57:20.712 --> 00:57:24.616
There were some scenes
that I couldn't even watch


620
00:57:24.683 --> 00:57:26.652
because they were too
disturbing.


621
00:57:33.692 --> 00:57:38.030
I started to feel like throwing
up,


622
00:57:38.096 --> 00:57:39.665
I didn't know what to do...

623
00:57:45.404 --> 00:57:47.005
To be honest,

624
00:57:48.540 --> 00:57:52.044
I was surprised
at how well-thought-out it was,


625
00:57:52.144 --> 00:57:57.516
even with that
constant injection of violence.


626
00:58:07.893 --> 00:58:12.898
It explains the whole
phenomenon of domination


627
00:58:12.965 --> 00:58:15.968
between people,
castes and classes,


628
00:58:16.068 --> 00:58:17.669
and the State's domination of
people.


629
00:58:44.196 --> 00:58:46.365
It was about a type of violence

630
00:58:46.465 --> 00:58:50.035
that we saw in the streets
quite often.


631
00:58:52.571 --> 00:58:56.008
In Valladolid,
we had friends in prison...


632
00:58:59.511 --> 00:59:01.179
and a friend who had been thrown

633
00:59:01.246 --> 00:59:03.849
from the window
of the Police station.


634
00:59:06.184 --> 00:59:10.622
That was what we saw
from 1971 or 1972


635
00:59:10.689 --> 00:59:13.825
up until the vote
for the constitution.


636
00:59:37.949 --> 00:59:39.985
It was a very disturbing film,

637
00:59:40.052 --> 00:59:43.388
one that doesn't leave you
indifferent.


638
00:59:43.455 --> 00:59:46.458
It caused a commotion,

639
00:59:46.525 --> 00:59:49.027
it's one of the films
that made the most noise.


